  "text": "After assessing growth at 37 C, two isolates were considered to be potential human pathogens and therefore excluded from further biosurfactant analysis. The initial screening step for biosurfactant production for all 138 isolates was by the use of the drop collapse assay [CITATION_1] . Swarming motility and white line-in-agar experiments were performed for all biosurfactant-producing isolates according to previously described methods (D'aes et al., 2011, 2014) .",
